_header: Labor in youth whilst health will last
_description: Proverbial couplet urging one to work in youth, rest in age — one couplet

GULHun230.Transcription:
Labur in youth qwylst helthe wyll lastTo rest in age qwen strengh is
                    past
GULHun230.Note: Added to end flyleaf by a sixteenth-century hand.
